  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3203922881" />
    <a title="W" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49365462-w"><img alt="W" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610208667p2/49365462.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3203922881?book_show_action=true">Feb 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="W" class="user" itemprop="url" name="W" href="/user/show/49365462-w">W</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49365462-w?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49365462-w?shelf=childhood">childhood</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3203922881" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14529629409789598238">First encountered as an Urdu translation,when I was a kid. Hugely enjoyable at the time,and memorable too.<br/><br/>Decided to revisit it,after all these years. It didn&apos;t disappoint. A scientist finds a way to become invisible,and dreams of the advantages it would bring him.<br/><br/>But a whole lot of undesirable,unintended consequences follow. He finds himself in trouble. Still,his cruelty and selfishness compel him to try and unleash a &quot;reign of terror&quot;.<br/><br/>Lively pace and good action. A quick read,fairly enjoyable,</span>
  <span id="freeText14529629409789598238" style="display:none">First encountered as an Urdu translation,when I was a kid. Hugely enjoyable at the time,and memorable too.<br /><br />Decided to revisit it,after all these years. It didn't disappoint. A scientist finds a way to become invisible,and dreams of the advantages it would bring him.<br /><br />But a whole lot of undesirable,unintended consequences follow. He finds himself in trouble. Still,his cruelty and selfishness compel him to try and unleash a "reign of terror".<br /><br />Lively pace and good action. A quick read,fairly enjoyable,all the more so because it was a trip down memory lane.<br /><br />3.5 stars</span>
  <a data-text-id="14529629409789598238" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


